# Frontend Rules (Mini Program)

Stack: Taro 4.2, React 18, TypeScript, Sass.

## Directory Structure

```
src/
├── pages/       page entry — thin, compose UI and state only
├── components/  reusable UI
├── services/    API calls — all HTTP requests live here
├── stores/      state management
├── utils/       pure functions — unit test targets
└── types/       shared TypeScript types
```

## Rules

- Pages must be thin: compose components, bind state, handle navigation.
- All API calls in `services/`; never call `Taro.request` directly in pages.
- Shared types in `types/`.
- Pure logic in `utils/` — write unit tests for these.
- Do not add UI snapshot tests in MVP.

## Testing Focus

- `services/` — request/response parsing, error code mapping
- `utils/` — pure function unit tests
- Skip component snapshot and WeChat DevTools E2E in MVP
